result.execSummary:
The defendant Vido A Nava was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).
  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).
  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
On Mr. Nava's Petition for Sentence Adjustment on Count #3: 
[MK] case called at 1:50pm. 
Defendant Vido A Nava appears by telephone from the Racine Correctional Institution. ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Mr. Nava makes a statement regarding his current programming completion being delayed, due to the facilitator being out on medical leave, to approximately October 21st.
Mr. Nava answers inquiries from the Court regarding the prison violation reports.  Mr. Nava indicates that his current release date is 9/12/17.
ADA Beck indicates that the State is opposing the Petition; arguments given by ADA Beck. 
The Court denies the Petition for Sentence Adjustment on Count #3. 
Mr. Nava makes a statement that he is still working toward being in a position to seek sentence adjustment when he nears the completion of the third consecutive sentence in this case. Mr. Nava requests that the Court grant that request now, in anticipation of Mr. Nava being at that point in serving time.  
The Court denies this request, explaining to Mr. Nava the time constraints for the filing of such a petition, and the victim rights notification that is involved and other factors.
recess 2:00pm.
